a |publisher=Panini}}\n* {{cite book |author=Carlo F. Chiesa|title=Il grande romanzo dello scudetto |publisher=da Calcio 2000 years 2002 and 2003}}\n* {{cite web|url= http://emeroteca.coni.it/?q=node%2F8|publisher=Corriere dello Sport|title= Stadio Il Littoriale, 1935 and 1936}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www3.lastampa.it/archivio-storico/|publisher=La Stampa|title= Championship 1935 and 1936}}\n\n== External Links ==\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/ital36.html|title=Serie A 1935-36 |publisher= Rsssf.com}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.federossoblu.com/it/almanacco/tabellini/286-tabellini-1935-36.html|title=Tabellini|publisher=Federossoblu.it}}\n\n{{Bologna F.C. 1909}}\n{{Bologna F.C. 1909 seasons}}\n{{1935\u201336 in Italian football}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1935\u201336 Bologna F.C.1909 season}}\n[[Category:Bologna F.C. 1909 seasons]]\n[[Category:Scudetto-winning seasons]]\n\n{{Italy-sport-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club season\n|club = [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna Associazione Giuoco del Calcio]]\n|season = 1935-36\n|manager = [[\u00c1rp\u00e1d Weisz]]\n|chairman = [[Renato Dall'Ara]]\n|chrtitle= President\n|stadium = [[Stadio Renato Dall'Ara|Stadio Littoriale]]\n|league = [[Serie A]]\n|league result = [[1935-36 Serie A|1\u00ba]] (in [[1936 Mitropa Cup|Mitropa Cup]])\n|cup1 = [[Coppa Italia]]\n|cup1 result = [[1935-36 Coppa Italia|Eightfinals]]\n|cup2 = [[Mitropa Cup]]\n|cup2 result  = [[1936 Mitropa Cup|Eightfinals]]\n|league topscorer = [[Angelo Schiavio]] (10)\n|season topscorer = [[Angelo Schiavio|Schiavio]] (11)\n\n|pattern_la1 = _bolognayears1930h\n|leftarm1 = 000066\n|pattern_b1 = _bolognayears1930h\n|body1 = FF0000\n|pattern_ra1 = _bolognayears1930h\n|rightarm1 = 000066\n|shorts1 = FFFFFF\n|socks1 = 000066\n\n|pattern_la2 = _borderonwhite\n|pattern_b2 = _bologna19311932a\n|pattern_ra2 = _borderonwhite\n|pattern_so2 = _double pale red line\n|leftarm2 = #FF0000\n|body2 = #FF0000\n|rightarm2 = #FF0000\n|shorts2 = FFFFFF\n|socks2 = 000066\n\n|prevseason = [[1934\u201335 Bologna F.C. 1909 season|1934\u201335]]\n|nextseason = [[1936\u201337 Bologna F.C. 1909 season|1936\u201337]]\n}}\nDuring the 1935-36 season '''Bologna Associazione Giuoco del Calcio''' competed in Serie A, Coppa Italia and [[Mitropa Cup]].\n\n== Summary ==\n\nThe club won its 3rd title<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dlib.coninet.it/bookreader.php?&c=1&f=2511&p=3#page/2/mode/2up|title=Presenze 1936|publisher=dlib.coninet.it}}</ref> ever after a closed race<ref>{{cite book|title=Almanacco Illustrato del Calcio - La Storia 1898-2004,|publisher= Panini Edizioni}}</ref>managed by hungarian coach Weisz. With 40 points over top of the table passed A.S. Roma (39), Torino (38) third place, Ambrosiana (36)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dlib.coninet.it/bookreader.php?&c=1&f=2615&p=5#page/4/mode/2up|publisher=dlib.coninet.it|title= 1936 calcio}}</ref> and Juventus fith with 35 points<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/ital36.html|publisher=RSSSF.com|title=Season 1935-36}}</ref>.\n\n== Squad ==\n{{fs start}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Mario Gianni]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Secondo Roggero]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giordano Corsi]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Dino Fiorini]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Felice Gasperi]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Mario Montesanto]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Michele Andreolo]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=''[[Amedeo Biavati]]''|pos=MF}}\n{{fs mid}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Aldo Donati]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Francisco Fedullo]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Raffaele Sansone]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Gerardo Ottani]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Bruno Maini]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Carlo Reguzzoni]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Angelo Schiavio]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Alcide Ivan Violi]]|pos=FW}}\n{